What you need to know:

She invested Sh200,000 in setting up greenhouses, labour, drip lines and buying seedlings.Greenhouse is a controlled environment, thus it helps increase yields.There is a huge demand in the European Union (EU) market especially in cities like London, which have a high Asian-Indian population and demand goes up during colder months.One should not focus on yields but give the plants the nutrition they need and they will produce more.